graphy in dialogue with digital photography and its own entangled economies of extraction, demonstrating the importance of understanding photography’s complicity in the economic, geopolitical, and social systems that order the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPhotographyxEnvironmental aspects. 0aPhotographyxEquipment and supplies. 0aPhotographyxHistory. 7aPhotography / Techniques / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311135689140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478059172?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478059172423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478059172/original  a978-3-11-135689-1  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles